ementClass()`, but if `classRef` is null, it falls back to creating a new instance with `Array.newInstance()`. This seems to make sense and could streamline how we handle class loading. I’ll need to ensure these caching mechanisms work correctly moving forward!\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "Implemented a dedicated test for the active dynamic-access class:\n\n- Added `tests/src/io.github.classgraph/classgraph/4.8.108/src/test/java/io_github_classgraph/classgraph/ArrayTypeSignatureTest.java`\n\nThe new test creates a detached `FieldInfo` descriptor for `String[][]`, obtains its `ArrayTypeSignature`, and exercises:\n\n- `ArrayTypeSignature.loadElementClass()` to reach the `Class.forName(String)` fallback path.\n- `ArrayTypeSignature.loadClass()` to reach `Array.newInstance(Class, int[])`.\n\nI did not compile or run tests, per instructions.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0d2e17a13e96ab0a016a028250e13c819d9146f11af2cf50fd\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 597, "output": 644, "cacheRead": 48128, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 49369, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1778549316319, "responseId": "resp_0d2e17a13e96ab0a016a02824529ac819dbc2da11ed334bd05"}, "toolResults": []}
